Perspective in Children's Games not only due to Vredeman de Vries, but interest also through P. Coecke's Serlio edition. See Serlio, livre II on perspective - Flemish translation published posthumously by Mayken Verhulst 1553, see [Georges] Marlier, [= La renaissance flamande: Pierre Coeck d'Alost, Bruxelles: Finck, 1966], Fig. 336, and p. 382, p. 383a: Dès 1558 Marie Verhulst fit réimprimer divers livres.

column4: <content>Perspective in Children's Games not only due to Vredeman de Vries, but interest also through P. Coecke's Serlio edition. See Serlio, livre II on perspective - Flemish translation published posthumously by Mayken Verhulst 1553, see [Georges] Marlier, [= La renaissance flamande: Pierre Coeck d'Alost, Bruxelles: Finck, 1966], Fig. 336, and p. 382, p. 383a: Dès 1558 Marie Verhulst fit réimprimer divers livres.</content>
